ACADEMIC USE AND CITATION
--------------------------

This software was developed as part of a scientific Master's thesis on
Single-Particle Tracking diffusion classification using Deep Learning.

If you use this software in academic work, please cite it appropriately.

For scientific publications, please reference:
- The original thesis/publication (when available)
- This repository: https://github.com/JulianLerch/CNN_forTrajectoryClassification

SCIENTIFIC REFERENCES
---------------------

This implementation is based on the following scientific literature:

[1] Granik, N., & Weiss, L. E. (2019). "Single-particle diffusion
    characterization by deep learning." Bioinformatics, 35(18), 3510-3517.

[2] Hochreiter, S., & Schmidhuber, J. (1997). "Long short-term memory."
    Neural Computation, 9(8), 1735-1780.

[3] Vaswani, A., et al. (2017). "Attention is all you need."
    Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems, 30.

[4] Michalet, X. (2010). "Mean square displacement analysis of single-particle
    trajectories with localization error." Physical Review E, 82(4), 041914.

[5] Kepten, E., et al. (2015). "Guidelines for the fitting of anomalous
    diffusion mean square displacement graphs." PLoS ONE, 10(2), e0117722.
